                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1160: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 31, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Your 68, January 30, 7 p.m. I am in favor of the cancellation of the arms
                    embargo to China. The United States has to do that by a proclamation of the
                    President which he can make at any time. Wire me if the Diplomatic Body are
                    ready to cancel the agreement and I will have the President issue a
                    proclamation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
